Sentencas: Residual stresses in the electrolytes of segmented-in-series solid oxide fuel cells (SIS-SOFCs) and anode-supported cells (ASCs) were estimated at room temperature by X-ray diffraction.
Titulo: Residual stress and redox cycling of segmented-in-series solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In the SIS-SOFCs, the residual stresses in the electrolyte were smaller than in the ASCs and did not change significantly after redox cycling.
Titulo: Residual stress and redox cycling of segmented-in-series solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For both designs, numerically calculated values of the residual stresses in the electrolyte were found to be comparable to the experimental results.
Titulo: Residual stress and redox cycling of segmented-in-series solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Next, in order to simulate the reoxidation reaction, the anode was subjected to forced expansion, and the residual stresses were estimated at high temperatures.
Titulo: Residual stress and redox cycling of segmented-in-series solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It was found that in the SIS-SOFC, the dimensional changes and residual stresses were smaller than those in the ASC.
Titulo: Residual stress and redox cycling of segmented-in-series solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The high redox tolerance of the SIS-SOFC is considered to stem from the fact that the electrically insulated substrate prevents the expansion and deformation of the positive electrode-electrolyte-negative electrode structure.
Titulo: Residual stress and redox cycling of segmented-in-series solid oxide fuel cells
